						<summary>

						<p>Slab lying near the Kēśva temple.</p>						

						<p>Vijayanagara: Sadāśiva.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is dated in Śaka 1491, Māgha, Śu. 15 (= A.D., 1570.)</p>						

						<p>Damaged. It records the grant of the <hi rend="italic">Vipravinōdi-Varttana</hi> made by a Vipravinōdin (name lost) for the merit of his father Govindaya, for the <hi rend="italic">amṛitapaḍi</hi> service to god.</p>						

						</summary>
